        "created_at": "2024-01-25T19:28:46.956Z",
        "cooked": "<p>It would be pretty cool if there was support for Google‚Äôs new <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/media/platform/hdr-image-format\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Ultra HDR standard</a>, as it‚Äôs the default now for Pixels and I think other phones will follow or also may already have it in some case, as it‚Äôs developed as a standard for Android. I don‚Äôt know what‚Äôs needed to support it as Android as a system should already have support for it with Android 14.</p>\n<p>Challenges right now maybe support what the image is touched by the app (I believe even images sent with the high quality are still recompressed or scaled) and maybe support on iOS if that is desired. For iOS libultrahdr cal maybe be used to get it as raw HDR yuv and display it. On desktop as Electron builds on Chrome Ultra HDR may already be supported, at least on Windows and maybe MacOS, HDR on Linux is still more or less pending on some Wayland improvements.</p>\n<p>If needed I can go get a sample file and you can also build your own using libultrahdr if you have an HDR and an SDR version of the same image (you could take a frame from an HDR video and a tonemapped version of that video for example or an Xbox Game Bar screenshot if you convert the JXR to AVIF).</p>",
