        "created_at": "2026-02-13T19:19:46.816Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I noticed that if I share an UltraHDR image from my phone, the image is displayed as HDR on the Signal Mac app - but not in the Android Signal app itself. If I download the picture from the Signal app, and open it in Gallery, it indeed is HDR (I can even see the HDR metadata EXIF).</p>\n<p>So this should be changed from ‚Äúadd support for android Ultra HDR‚Äù to ‚ÄúDisplay HDR images as HDR‚Äù, since images are already sent as HDR.</p>",
